 Former Governor of Abia State and Chief Whip of the Senate, Senator Orji Kalu has felicitated with former President Goodluck Jonathan on the occasion of his 63rd birthday anniversary.  Extolling the virtues of the celebrant, Kalu commended the former Nigerian leader for his contributions to the social, economic and political development of the nation.   He described the former President as a compassionate politician and patriotic statesman, who is committed to a united, indivisible and prosperous Nigeria.    While wishing the formee president longer life in sound health, the former Governor extended his greetings to family, friends and associates of Jonathan.  Kalu in a goodwill message said, “I join other  Nigerians in celebrating a patriotic and selfless statesman, former President Goodluck Jonathan as he clocks 63.    “Having served Bayelsa state and Nigeria in various capacities, your immense contributions to nation building are worthy of commendation and emulation.  “Your Excellency, as you mark your birthday, it is my prayer that God will continue to strengthen you in the service of humanity”. Kalu wished the former President a joyous celebration.